  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In patients with acute rejection after lung transplantation the peptide profile in
      broncho-alveolar lavage (BAL) and urine should be compared in order to identify a paradigm
      that allows an non-invasive rejection therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Goal of the study is the establishment of biomarkers for early diagnosis of acute rejection,
      followed by a late validation of the paradigm with prospectively collected samples, which
      will be examined blinded.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
